    "defect_id": "UEFIRM-70862",
    "key": "UEFIRM-70862",
    "summary": " \"ACPI errors\" in system logs with SR250V2& ST250V2",
    "severity": "Medium",
    "platform_found": "Trenton",
    "project_found": "[9562] FW On-Demand Release 25C",
    "priority": "Medium",
    "status": "Closed",
    "resolution": "Done",
    "solution_explanation": "In the Intel reference code of Tatlow, once enabling the HWP, highest frequency will be reported up to OS via _CPC as below: \r\n------  \r\nStore(_SB.LMPS, DeRefOf(Index(CPC2,2)))\r\n\r\n------\r\n\r\nbut using DeRefOf seems not available for overriding data into package, it should be Index instead.",
    "build_fixed": "TQE121C",
    "root_cause": "If setting \"CPU P-state Control\" to Autonomous , customers will find these error messages from dmesg log in Redhat 9.2 or later versions.\r\n\r\n ACPI Error: Needed type [Reference], found [Buffer] 00000000ad729782 (20230331/exresop-66)\r\nACPI Error: AE_AML_OPERAND_TYPE, While resolving operands for [OpcodeName unavailable] (20230331/dswexec-433)\r\nACPI Error: Aborting method \\_SB.PR00._CPC due to previous error (AE_AML_OPERAND_TYPE) (20230331/psparse-529)",
    "assignee": "Steve CY Hsu",
    "reporter": "Jinzhu JZ10 Zhang",
